inn1.comm: better, pitched up on off stump and Tharanga defends off the front foot
similar ball, Tharanga pushes towards extra cover and sets off for the run, risky but he's quick to get to the other end
good ball, right upto him and he defends off the front foot into the covers
first runs off the bat, angled away from off stump, he drops the hands and squeezes one past gully for runs
good movement, pitched up on middle and off, worked to the on side
good ball, very close to off stump, Jayasuriya defends but gets an inside edge very close to the stumps, good, tidy over that
good length on the stumps, pushed towards cover and they pinch a single
wider this time outside off stump, and its a no-ball
good ball, sharp on a good length outside off stump, defended
good length again, pushed down the ground and Yousuf moves around from mid-off and fields
width offered, Tharanga cuts loosely but the ball bounces near his feet, Kamran Akmal and first slip move forward and collect it
width again and he punches off the back foot to point, no run there
middle and off this time and he defends off the back foot to cover, who swoops i and fields&
short and wide, Jayasuriya hops and cracks that over extra cover, ball goes in the air but lands safely in the end
outside off, steered towards gully who dives and saves runs
beaten going for a drive by one that lands outside off stump and swings away
middle and off, driven hard to mid-on who dives to his right and stops it
fullish outside off stump, defended to cover
middle and leg, tucked off the pads to Razzaq at deep backward square leg
same line, worked down to deep backward square leg again
full on off stump, defended towards Hafeez at point, who's quite sharp
full outside off again, driven straight to Yousuf at mid-off
walks down the wicket, picks the length well and drives that through the covers for four, positive shot that
good ball, quick outside off stump, Jayasuriya stands and pokes at it, ball whizzes  by and beats the bat, bowler goes up in appeal but there wasn't any bat on that one
full outside off stump, Tharanga drives and gets an outside edge through gully and down to wide third man
outside off, he hops again and just jabs that in the off side gap and the ball just speeds away for four, all power
dropped in short on middle and leg, pulled on the ground to Afridi who dives and makes a mess of it, allows the ball to squeeze through midwicket
full on middle and off, defended back towards the bowler's left
good ball, outside off and some bounce there, surprises Jayasuriya who pokes at it and the ball rolls towards slip
full outside off stump, pushed to Yousuf at mid-off
good length outside off, Tharanga stands and punches that in the gap between cover and mid-off and runs hard, they get three in the end, well run
width offered, Jayasuriya throws everything at it but misses as the ball keeps low
good ball, right upto him on off stump, he just drops the ball and runs, midwicket moves in quickly as does short cover, but it was well placed and they get a run
full outside off, gets onto the front foot and drives through cover, opened the face on that one, an athletic Shoaib Malik sets off and hauls it in
middle and leg this time, ball stays low but Tharanga plays straight and negotiates it to the on side
fullish on off stump, steered towards Hafeez at point and he wants the run but Jayasuriya sends him back
not even that short outside off stump, but he effortless latches onto it and drives that to the left of point for another four, top shot, little followthough, a mere dab that

wow! Dropped in short as he saw Jayasuriya get onto the front foor, its a no-ball too, but he sees that and swivels on the hook and gets that high over deep backward square leg for maximum, this man is so quick with his hands
better, fullish outside off, defended to cover
again he sees him come forward and drops it short, Jayasuriya pulls but gets a top-edge off the chest, ball goes high in the air towards square leg but the fielders cant get to it
good length outside off, pushed towards Hafeez at point, sets out and is sent back, Hafeez fires in a throw that hits but he was safely in
poor ball, banged in short on leg stump, Jayasuriya pulls that and gets bat onto it, ball screams down to fine leg for four
full outside off this time, driven hard in the gap at cover, fielder gives chase and just pulls it in on the ropes, good over for Sri Lanka, poor for Rana and his side
good length on off, defended towards Hafeez at point, loud call of 'NO' back to Tharanga
good ball, middle and off, pushed to mid-off who comes in and fields, no chance of a run on that occasion
oh boy, here he goes again! Jayasuriya walks down the ground and smashes that clean as a whistle straight down the ground for six and thats Sri Lanka's 50 up in no time
full outside off, a true cricketing stroke, gets onto the front foot and drives that past Yousuf at mid-off for four, great to watch
short outside off, drives and gets an edge past the vacant gully for one
and Tharanga joins the fun! Full outside off, as easy as they come, and he drives that on the up in the gap at cover for four, a fine over for Sri Lanka
good length ball outside off stump, pushed off the back foot to Hafeez at point
shorter on middle and leg, again he tries to pull but gets clipped on the pads, ball rolls to the leg side

dropped! Short again, he pulls hard towards Afridi at short midwicket, shouts of 'CATCH IT' there as the ball goes in and out of his hands, was hit hard and to his left, but he failed to latch on, costly? Umar doesnt like it one bit...
a bouncer, good thinking from Gul, Tharanga down on his haunches to avert danger
fuller outside off, driven to Malik at cover who moves to his left and fields
good length ball on off, Tharanga stands tall and defends to Malik

and he gets the man they wanted! A relatively harmless ball, straight on the stumps, Jayasuriya has an ugly swipe across the line and loses his composure and stumps, vital strike from Iftikhar, who lets forth a nice verbal volley at Jayasuriya as he passes him, much fun!
good ball, full on off and shaping into him, but worked around the corner with soft hands for a quick two, runs immediately for Jayawardene
full again, a good-looking drive to Yousuf at mid-on
good stuff again, right on the stumps, Jayawardene defends back towards mid-on again
good length outside off, Jayawardene drops the hands and rolls it towards point
drifts to middle and off, tucked to the onside to where Maliks comes in and fields

oops! Good length outside off stump, Tharanga pokes at it and gets an edge, but the ball flies between Akmal and Afridi at first slip and runs away for runs, thats a massive gap there between the two men, where's Younis? He's the better slipper!
middle and leg, worked to midwicket for a run
full on middle and off, pushed to Yousuf at mid-on
good stuff, right upto him outside off, no room to drive or cut and Jayawardene defends with a dead bat, good cricket
fuller and wider this time, and quicker too, Jayawardene goes for a drive but misses
fuller on middle and leg, flicked in the midwicket gap, not in control of that shot, Afridi and Yousuf give chase but the batsmen steal a brace
good length ball on off stump, defended to mid-off
good ball again, Tharanga quickly goes back and pushes to mid-off again
fuller on this occasion but he gets on top of it and pushes to mid-off once more
a fraction shorter on the stumps and Tharanga gets into position early and swivel-pulls that through square leg and gets four to his name, thats not the line to bowl with a 6-3 field
full on the pads, worked away down to fine leg
right upto him on off stump and he pushes that down to Yousuf at mid-on
short outside off stump, cracked hard but right to Malik at cover
good length on off stump, defended to Malik in the covers
fuller outside off, Tharanga gets on top and drives to mid-off
short on this occasion, he swivels and pulls down to Rana at deep backward square leg
short again, Jayawardene goes for a pull, ball doesnt bounce that much at all and he misses, Akmal collects it
fuller, a low full toss actually but he can't cash in, ends up driving to Yousuf at mid-on
short and wide and Tharangas has a hard waft at it, makes no contact at all
short on middle and off, worked to Rana at deep midwicket

full on off stump, whipped in the air past square leg, sets off for two, fielder moves across from fine leg, fields, and fires in the throw to Akmal, umpire goes upstairs but its confirmed that Jayawardene was back in
short and wide, steered down to third man, another single
this one lands outside off and bounces, Tharanga drives and then tries to take the hands off it, ball pops up in the air but lands safely in front of point
full and driven hard to Malik at extra cover
good ball first-up from the drinks break, Jayawardene stands and defends with soft hands and a dead bat
short again, and sits up at that slower pace, easily pulled through square leg for two more
shot! Full outside off stump, Jayawardene frees the arms and slams that over cover for four, thats 6,000 ODI runs for the man, fine shot
better ball, a good length outside off stump, Jayawardene stands and keeps that down to his feet with a dead bat
well bowled again, identical ball and Jayawardene up on his toes in defence
full outside off, driven loosely to Hafeez at point
bad ball to begin with, width offered outside off stump and its carved past point for four first-up, good shot
middle and leg, worked to Rana at mid-on
fullish outside off, just slogged away through midwicket for four more
short, he pulls that through square leg and down to the man on the fence, did well to roll the wrists and keep it down
leg stump and it hits the pads, loud appeal but that pitched outside the line, Billy B shakes his head as the batsmen pinch a leg bye
slower this time, Jayawardene falls over in his shot, ball clips the pad, again Razzaq and 'keeper appeal but that was missing leg
outside off, driven well to Hafeez who dives to his right at point
outside off again, stands and punches to point again
full on the stumps, pushed down the ground, mid-off comes around and fields, thats the 100 for Sri Lanka
good length outside off stump, defended towards point
slower and fuller outside off stump, Jayawardene goes for an ugly swipe across the line but mistimes that to mid-on
fullish outside off stump, driven on the up to cover
full on off stump and its driven back to the bowler
fullish outside off stump, Tharanga sees the width and flashes at it, ends up losing control as he throws himself at it, takes one hand off it but has enough to send it high and down to wide long-off
much better shot, full and he caresses that in the gap at point, ball speeds away to the fence, good one
gone! Fullish again outside off stump, again Tharanga tries that booming drive but gets a thick outside edge which Akmal gladly snaps up, Razzaq strikes after going for runs
angled across him from outside off, left alone with ease
a fraction short outside off stump and he stands and thwacks that off the middle of the bat between cover and point for four, what a way to get off the mark
good ball outside off stumps, defended to point, they steal a quick run
short again, he stands and unleashes a splendid back-foot drive past cover for another boundary, thats two sumptious fours for Sangakarra
drifts to middle and leg and he easily tucks that around the corner for a couple
right upto him on off, defended to mid-off
fraction slower outside off, pushed to Hafeez at point
fuller on off, turned to square leg who moves in fast
bad ball, swings down leg for Akmal to collect
middle and leg, tucked to midwicket
outside off, Jayawardene stands tall and defends
middle and leg, tries to work it fine but mistimes it, ball pops towards point, Sangakkara calls for the run and they steal it
outside off stump, stands tall and pushes to short cover

dragged in short, ball stands up, Sangakkara swivels and pulls that high over midwicket, ball lands near the ropes and rolls ever so slowly over them as the fielder's a fraction late in reaching there
fuller outside off stump, pushed to mid-off
slow on middle and off, turned around the corner for one
tossed up on off, defended back to the bowler
again tossed up on off, pushed back to Malik's right
flighted outside off, gives the charge and drives to mid-off
tossed up outside off, Jayawardene gets forward and paddles that around the corner for four, a fine shot
goes back and tries to run that down fine, but the man at gully is too sharp
slow on middle and leg, tucked to square leg with ease
short and wide, cut hard but right to Hafeez at point
short again and this time he finds the gap at gully and gets one down to third man
tossed up, pushed to short mid-on
flighted again, walks down and drives to mid-on for one
slightly short, he latches onto it and cuts down to the deep extra cover sweeper and gets one more to his name
tossed up outside off, swept hard past square leg for another
outside off stump, steered to Razzaq at gully
flatter this time on the stumps, pushed back to Malik
flat and short, but all he can do is go back and push back to Malik
pushed down the leg side and its flicked to square leg for one
quick and short outside off stump, he goes back and cuts that to the fielder in the deep, singles ticking along here
quicker outside off, he drives but gets an inside edge to the on side
short outside off, the offspinner, and its cut hard to the off side
flighted on middle and off, turned to the on side
beats the bat, Sangakkara expected that to turn a lot more
full outside off, pushed to mid-off

and he gets the wicket! Tossed up outside off stump, Jayawardene again sweeps that but gets a top-edge which Farhat snaps up moving back and to his left at leg gully, crucial breakthrough for Pakistan, Sri Lanka's captain departs for 31
full outside off stump, pushed to mid-off for one first ball
drifting down the legs, worked fine for another quick single
defended off the front foot
came down the track, ball was held back a bit, adjusted to push it to midwicket
outside the off, pushed to cover
slipping down the leg side, Akmal can't get to it ...
floated on the off and middle, pushed down the track
slightly flatter, on the off, steered to backward point
on the middle and leg, tickled to the on side
on the middle, turning in slightly, worked around the corner
fullish, pushed down the ground.
slightly short and outside off, cut to short third man
floated outside off, driven to long-on
slower and on a length, no pace to work with. pushed to the on side
pushed to on side
length delivery on the off, pushed to point
short and on the hips, flicked past square-leg
pushes it down the pitch, wants a run, Maharoof sends him back in a hurry.
dropped! Came down the track and hit straight back to bowler, he stretches his hands out but can't hold it.
outside off, pushed to cover point and they run with the stroke
comes down the track to drive it down to long-on
just outside off, on a length, steered to fine thirdman

Gone... Atapattu is hit on the pads as he tries to work to on side and sets off for a run but Maharoof sends him back. But Atapattu fails to make it time to beat the throw from Hafeez who swooped in from point

inn2.comm: full on middle and leg, Hafeez clips it well through mid-on, Muralitharan gives chase and hauls it in near the ropes, batsmen run three
beaten by one that lands outside off and seams away, good ball
half volley outside off stump, Farhat stands and drives that through the off side for four, great shot
full outside off, pushed to point
good pace, good line and length, beats the bat outside off stump, little shape away on that ball
drifts to leg, Hafeez clips that down to fine leg where Vaas dives very well and saves a certain four
just down leg, a wide, Sangakkara dives to his left and takes it cleanly
good length outside off stump, Farhat brings the bat down quickly and defends back to the bowler
glorious shot! Full and fast outside off stump, a rank halfvolley, and Farhat bring the bat down like a rapier and unleashes a firm straight drive back down the ground for four
full outside off, punched to Murali at mid-off, they steal a quick run
middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
full and swinging away outside off, left alone
rank halfvolley and its smashed past a diving Maharoof at mid-off for four, well struck by Hafeez
worked into the gap at mid-off again, a couple runs taken
full outside off, pushed to mid-off
wide, swings down leg for Sangakkara to collect
fullish outside off, Hafeez leans into and finds the gap at gully for four
wide and swinging away, Sangakkara, standing upto the stumps, collects it
width, and Hafeez punches that through extra cover off the backfoot, wonderful shot

but he's gone this time! A lovely length ball outside off, Hafeez goes forward and opens the face, half-cock, and gets a thin edge right into Sangakkara's gloves, the ploy to stand upto the stumps works
full outside off, driven to Fernando at mid-off
full and moving away outside off, left alone
full outside off, driven along the ground to cover
full on off, driven back to the bowler
full on leg stump, turned around the corner to the man at leg gully
full and going down leg, Farhat gets down and swings at it, misses
good length ball on the stumps, Younis hops and defends back to the bowler
full on middle and leg, Younis flicks and gets an inside edge onto the pads
full on middle and off, flicked airily through that gap at mid-on and midwicket, Murali gives chase and saves a four
full and driven to cover
full on off, driven back to the bowler
drifts to middle and leg, Younis gets on top of it and flicks it handsomely through mid-on for four, got right on top of it, head still, and used the pace of the ball
drifts down leg, flicked well down to the ropes where the fielder moves fast and cuts it off, batsmen get two anyway
short outside off, stands and steers that through gully
full and driven back to the bowler
full and its slashed to Dilshan at backward point
full outside off, the slower offcutter, Farhat has a full swing at it but misses all ends up
good length ball jags into him, defended to point
dead full on the stumps, Younis drives back down the ground, Fernando gets a finger to it and slows down the pace
and its a full toss outside off stump, which Farhat duly dispatches firmly through point and cover for four more, Fernando got the split-fingered delivery all wrong
dropped! Flashes at a wide one outside off stump, and Jayawardene puts down a dolly moving low to his left, the ball hit him high on the palm and popped out, oops!
full outside off stump, Farhat has a free swing of the arms and slams that over mid-on for four, risky but effective
fullish outside off, Farhat gets into great position and smashes that through the off side, good shot on the up

and he strikes first ball, can you believe it! Lands this outside off stump, a fraction short of a good length, a little seam movement there, forces Younis to go for a drive and nibble through to Sangakarra! Maharoof's magic continues, second wicket down for Pakistan
fine shot, smashes a halfvolley outside off through the gap at extra cover, as easy as they come but still a treat to watch
fullish outside off stump, Farhat has a massive smash at that and sends it high over the off side field for four
full outside off stump again, Farhat produces a much better cricket shot on the up, a flowing extra cover drive sends the ball speeding away to the ropes
short of a length outside off stump, turns that fine for a quick single

short outside off stump, Yousuf stands up on his toes and slices that past gully to third man, where the big man Fernando runs hard, gets a hand to the ball, but fumbles and allows it to trickle over the rope, comedic stuff down there, poor chap
begins with a no-ball, tossed up outside off stump, Farhat gets forward and swats that through square leg for two, takes advantage of the big gap on the on side
tossed up outside off, defended off the front foot
fraction shorter, Farhat goes back and cuts right to Dilshan at backward point
tossed up, Farhat goes to sweep, ball parries off the gloves to the on side, no fielder there
tossed up outside off stump again, swept hard down to fine leg
tossed up outside off, Yousuf gets forward and tucks that to the man at leg gully
well tossed up again, Yousuf gets forward and turns that to the onside, fielder moves in so no chance of a run
tossed up outside off, Farhat drives and gets an inside edge to square leg, thats the 100 up for Pakistan and the 50 for Farhat, well played
going down leg, swept but right to leg slip
flatter outside off, driven back to the bowler
tossed up, driven hard to Dilshan at short cover
tossed up on off stump, turned to the on side
tossed up on off, Yousuf gets forward and defends, Farhat wants the run but is sent back
again Farhat likes the sweep against Murali, dangerous but he pulls it off again with a firm swipe through midwicket, they jog through for one
comes forward to one outside off stump and defends it
turns this from outside off stump to the onside, fielder swoops in and they resist the run
again Yousuf works this from outside off to the on side, no chance for a run again
fraction shorter and keeping low, he goes back and tries to cut but misses
the doosra spins away from his bat as he lunges forward, well bowled
charges and drives to the  off side where Jayawardene dives and saves runs
full on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
flatter, Yousuf uses the feet and drives down to long-on
tossed up outside off stump,  Farhat reverse sweeps right to the man at gully
gives him the charge, swings wildly but doesnt time it well, ball rolls along the ground to long-on

and it works! Holy cow, that was so predictable! Tossed up outside off stump, Farhat gives the charge, doesnt get under it and lofts that high and down to Fernando at long-off, what a stupid shot and he's handed the game back to Sri Lanka
tossed up on off stump, turned to the on side
width offered, he cuts that past slip for four
short again, Yousuf makes room and cuts past gully again
lands outside off and spins into the pads, they all let out a large appeal, umpire Taufel says sorry mate, youre flat in my way, I cant see it, I cant give it, was probably missing off stump anyway
tossed up, driven to mid-on
flatter on the stumps, comes forward and drives to mid-on
slower through the air, Yousuf defends back to the bowler
tossed up, swept around the corner for a single down to Malinga
swept down to backward square leg
tossed up, spins into the pads, Afridi plays over it, Murali appeals, some bat on that methinks
beaten coming forward by the doosra that spins away
spins sharply into him, quicker ball too, Afridi manages to keep it out
full on off, defended
spins into him this time, he appeals but that was spinning down leg
tossed up, flicked to midwicket

Afridi's madness! Tossed up, comes down the track, there we have the one leg going up, doesnt pick the ball at all, and ends up smashing that high and down to long-off for a simple catch to Tharanga, why was Afridi sent up to face the spinners on this track?
tossed up, driven in the air on the off side, where's the fielder?
tossed up, comes forward and defends
short outside off stump, steered to gully for a single
middle stump, flicked to Tharanga at square leg who dives to his left
short and wide, Malik stands tall and cuts to point
quicker outside off and moves into him, Malik hops in his crease and defends
short and its cut to Jayasuriya at point
fuller and he defends it back to the bowler
swings down leg, Sangakkara makes a mess of it and allows it to run away, wides signalled
Kicked up from a length and beat the intended prod
fullish outside off, Yousuf leant forward and guided it with softhands between slip and the 'keeper
outside off, moves away, pushed to cover. Sangakkara is standing upto the stumps
just outside off, off cutter, pushed to cover
on the middle. turned to midwicket
fullish outside off, cut to thirdman
on the legs, tries to flick it away but is rapped on the pads
fullish on the off, driven down the ground
length delivery just outside off, Yousuf stays where he is and just pushes it towards point
banged in short, outside off, and Yousuf pulls it, makes contact with the bottom of the bat and it goes to right of square-leg fielder who dives to make a good stop
length delivery just outside off, Yousuf tries to tap it close and run but is sent back
just outside off, short of length, Yousuf punches it towards mid-off, initially thinks about a run but decides against it
much fuller, outside off and Yousuf slices it, in the air,  through cover point
right on target, coming in from outside off, Yousuf is struck on the pads as he pushes onto his front foot. They go up in appeal but its outside the line
leans forward to push a ball towards mid-on and runs with the stroke
on the legs, full, flicked past square-leg
slower ball, fullish, outside off, square-driven to right of Dilshan at point who dives full length to make the stop
overpitched on the off stump line and Yousuf drives to mid-on where Malinga moves quickly to his left to make a diving stop
short and outside off, cut past point
on the off and middle, pushed to on side
turns in from outside off, driven back to the bowler
tossed up on the middle and off, fullish, worked down the ground to long-on
tossed up on the off, Yousuf puts his front foot forward, drives it to long-on
again bit overpitched, and again long-on comes into play. Maybe the dew is hindering Murali a bit. He just towelled his hands and the ball dry before this ball
just outside off, cut past point
on the middle, turning away slightly, pushed to the off side and away they run
floated on the leg and middle, worked to midwicket
slightly slower on the middle and leg, fullish, driven to long-on
comes in with the angle, from outside off, steered towards cover point
The singles are coming steadily. on the middle, fullish, driven to long-on
held back a bit and much slower through  the air, Yousuf adjusts and just blocks it.
full and on the middle, turned to midwicket
doosra on the off, Shoaib backs away to cut it past point
leans forward to smother the spin.
just outside off, pushed towards point
tossed up outside off, Yousuf tries to work it to on side and is rapped on the pads
doosra, tossed up outside off, Yousuf stretches forward in defence, gets an outside edge which takes the ball to shortish thirdman
speared in on the middle and leg, full in length, turned past square-leg
floated on the middle and leg, swept to short fineleg
comes in with the angle, on the off and middle, Yousuf gets an inside edge onto his pads
another inside edge, to midwicket, as Yousuf plays for the non existent spin
Yousuf comes down the track, Jayasuriya holds back the length and just pushed away to the off side
comes down the track and almost yorks himself, but gets it to point
rips in a offbreak on the middle, reverse swept to short thirdman
on the middle, worked to midwicket
flighted delivery on the middle and off, Shoaib leans forward to drive it down the ground
tickled around the corner to shortish fine-leg.
slower through the air, on the middle and leg, paddled to the on side

Oh what chaos! Misfield results in a run out. Youhana tickles a shortish delivery behind square-leg. They run two and Fernando, coming in from long-leg, fails to pick the ball and over runs a bit! Yousuf sees the chance to steal a extra run, sets off but Shoaib sends him back. It was too late by then. What a way to go. This could really set the cat among the pigeons.
fullish on the middle, driven down the ground
slower through the air, outside the off stump, cut to short thirdman
fullish on the middle, Akmal leans forward and using the bottom-hand turns it to left of midwicket where a tumbling stop is made
just outside off, Akmal pushes it towards point, wants a single but is quickly sent back
floated up on the middle, driven down the ground. That has been the most profitable area for Pakistan in the recent overs.
outside off, drawing Akmal forward who stretches in front of his body, and drives it to right of the sweeper cover
floated up full on the off, driven to deep cover.
straight one on the middle, pushed to midwicket
fullish on the middle and off, driven to long-on
again a bit overpitched, driven down the ground.
on the legs, tickled to short fine-leg
tossed up full, on the middle and leg, Akmal gets outside the line and drives it to long-on
again the dew comes into play. A low full-toss but Malik couldn't put it away. sweeps it straight to deep midwicekt
on a length, outside off, driven to long-off
short and outside off, cut past point
spears in full and straight on the middle, pushed back down the track
full and on the middle, driven back to the bowler
outside off, steered to point
straight one on the middle, driven to long-on.
another straight one on the off, square-driven past point. Dilshan unable to spin the wet ball.
long hop on the leg, should have been put away for a boundary, instead pulled to long-leg
on the middle and leg, turned past midwicket, they seemed to amble across for the first run before suddenly the possibility of the second hit them and they charged through to make it.
short of length, slower through the air and it comes in with the angle, Akmal goes back to punch it to long-on
tossed up on the off and middle, driven inside out to extra cover
again tossed up on the off, driven straight to extra cover
slightly quicker, full in length, square-driven past point
floated on the middle and off, Malik, once again, chooses to go inside out, towards long-off.
on the middle, Akmal goes back to a fullish delivery and turns it to midwicket
turns in from the off and middle, and raps Akmal on the pads as he tries to flick it away
pushes to point
slow through the air, the ball took an eternity to arrive, pushed to point
almost a run out as Malik pushed to cover and wants a run but is sent back in time
Malik advances down the track to heave a tossed up one to deep midwicket. Maharoof moves smartly to his left and restricts it just to a single

dropped! but a very difficult chance. Akmal goes for a sweep, and gloves it. Sangakkara is moving to his left when the ball bounds off the gloves to his right. he stretches his hand out but ends up palming it off
whack! slightly short and Akmal goes back to punch it inside out past extra cover.
outside off, full in length, leans forward to push it to long-on
swept to squareleg and the singles keep coming. Pakistan are approaching this sensibily.
Thwack! Malik advances down the track as Murali releases the wet ball and lofts it  cleanly over long-on.
Murali comes back with a ripping doosra that beats Malik.
fires in a quick one that spins in and Malik is rapped on the pads. Good contest on.

He gets it but the credit goes to Maharoof who ran some twenty yards to his left from deep midwicket to hold on to a very good catch. It was a short delivery and Akmal pulled it from outside the off stump and it looked like maximum when he connected. But a damn good catch at the end once again threatens to tilt the scales back on this roller coaster of a match.
Overpitched outside off, driven through Jayawardene at cover
Vaas goes up in appeal as Malik is rapped on the pads but it was going down leg and high as well.
on the middle and leg, tucked behind square-leg
almost waist-high full-toss, pushed past square-leg. Malik loses his right shoe as he sets for that run and hobbles across with one shoe!
fires in one way down the leg side, Sangakkara fails to gather it cleanly
beaten outside off. Razzak plays for more spin than what was on offer and ends up pushing inside the line
outside off, steered to thirdman
goes back to a length delivery that turns in a bit and keeps it away
again goes back to push one to midwicket
outside the off stump, steered to short thirdman
Murali almost gets a wicket off his last ball. A doosra that kept a touch low had Malik groping at it but the ball whizzes beneath his blade
fullish on the off stump, driven to sweeper cover. One more run.
another run as Malik drives a fullish delivery out to long-off

dropped! Would you believe it, its Dilshan, probably the best Sri Lankan fielder. Fullish outside off and Razzak goes for a squaredrive off a slower one but can't keep it down. Dilshan stretches his hands out but can't hold it. Fairly simple chance for a good point fielder.
on the middle and off, dead-batted away
off cutter on the off stump, Razzak uses his wrists well to glide it to thirdman
The round-arm flinger starts off with a beauty. Attempted yorker that shaves past the leg stump and Sangakkara throws himself to his left to gather it.
Razzaq comes back with a lovely inside-out drive. in the slot and he crashes it past extra cover
Malinga fires in another one almost at the blockhole, jabbed down the track
ooh almost caught. Fullish and Razzaq clips it in the air to left of straightish midwicket where Murali dives but can't quite reach it
Again Malinga pings the fullish length, Razzaq backs away to drive to sweeper cover. Well timed and it races across the turf but hit straight to the man in the deep
full, on the off, Malik taps it close to the off side, wants a run. Malinga charges across, Razzaq sends Malik back who flings himself back into the crease.
big heave ho but goes straight to long-on.  Vaas's last over in progress.
Malik backs away from the stumps and lofts a fullish delivery inside-out to wide long-off.
Whack! Razzaq creams a lofted six over long-off! Full and he backed away to cream it straight.  what a shot!

Malik puts Pakistan further in front with a lovely flick. Attempted yorker ends up fullish on the legs and with the fine-leg up all Malik had to do was send it to right of him. He does it pretty well.

almost a mix-up. Bill Lawry would have been screaming in joy if he were here. Fullish on the middle and leg, pushed to straightish midwicket, Razzaq, from the non-striker's end, wants a run, Malik doesn't , Jayawardene, who fielded the ball, wishes they ran! but Malik sends Razzaq back in time
bang! sliced over point. Gets his left foot out of the line and slices it over
Murderous assault on!  Takes his front foot outside the line again and wallops it straight and clean through the line
Goes for another big one, a slice over cover but doesn't time it well and it lands in no man's land. I suspect if he had connected well it might have gone down the deep cover's throat
Malik does the sensible thing by pushing one towards long-on. Easy single.
slower ball but Razzaq spots it early, waits for the ball to arrive to cut it past point.
There he goes again. Another whack, wants to finish it off in style,  but can't get under the ball and it rolls towards long-on.

What a great win! Razzaq finishes it off in style. Almost a nonchalant hit. He takes his left foot out of the line, and creams a fullish delivery over long-off. The white ball screams over the boundary
